{{defn|1=A row of small figures along the unions of the roofs of Chinese official buildings. }}

{{term|1=Interlaced arches}}
{{defn|1=A scheme of decoration employed in [[Romanesque architecture|Romanesque]] and [[Gothic architecture|Gothic]] architecture, where [[arch]]es are thrown from alternate [[Pier (architecture)|piers]], interlacing or intersecting one another. In the former case, the first arch [[Molding (decorative)|mould]] is carried alternately over and under the second, in the latter the mouldings actually intersect and stop one another.<ref>{{Cite EB1911|wstitle=Interlaced Arches|short=1|volume=14|page=693}}</ref>}}

{{term|1= Ionic order |content= [[Ionic order]] }}
{{defn|1=One of the three [[Classical order|orders]] or organisational systems of Ancient Greek or classical architecture characterised by columns which stood on the flat pavement of a temple with a base, their vertical shafts fluted with parallel concave grooves topped by a [[Capital (architecture)|capital]] with [[volute]]s, that flared from the column to meet a rectangular [[Abacus (architecture)|abacus]] with carved [[ovolo]] moulding, at the intersection with the horizontal beam that they carried. }}
{{glossary end}}

