'''Guatemalan Sign Language''' is the national [[deaf sign language]] used in [[Guatemala]]. The first dictionary was published in 2000. It is distinct from the sign languages used in Mexico and other neighboring [[Spanish language|Spanish speaking]] countries, and from [[Mayan sign languages#Highland Maya Sign Language|Highland Maya Sign Language]], which is used among [[K'iche' people|K'iche' Maya]] of rural Guatemala.

