{{BLP sources|date=October 2017}} {{Infobox writer | name = Namdev Tarachandani | image = | image_size = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | pseudonym = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1946|11|25}} | birth_place =Lukman, British India (now in [[Khairpur district]], [[Pakistan]]) | occupation = poet, writer, scholar | language = [[Sindhi language|Sindhi]] | residence = [[Vadodara]], [[Gujarat]] | nationality = Indian | awards = [[Sahitya Akademi Award]] (2013) | signature = | website = {{Official website}} }}
'''Namdev Tarachandani''' is a [[Sindhi language]] writer and scholar from India. He lives in [[Vadodara]], Gujarat, India. He was born on 25 November 1946 in Lukman (now in [[Khairpur district]], [[Pakistan]]).
''Jora-Kata'' (1974) is a novel written by him. It is translated into [[Gujarati language|Gujarati]] as ''Vatta-Ochha'' (1980). ''Vikhoon'' (1981) and ''Paglan'' (1991) are his collections of short story while ''Athon-Sur'' (1984) and ''Manush Nagri'' (2011) are his poetry collections. His critical works includes ''Sindhi Katha Sahitya'' (2004) and ''Sach Chavan Ji Chhoot'' (2011).<ref name="Welcome to Sahitya Akademi">{{cite web | title=Who's Who of Indian Writers | website=[[Sahitya Akademi]] | url=http://sahitya-akademi.gov.in/sahitya-akademi/SASearchSystem/sauser/writerinfo.jsp?wrids=639 | access-date=2017-10-17}}</ref> He received [[Sahitya Akademi Award]] (2013) for his book ''Manush Nagri''.<ref name="Jagranjosh.com 2013">{{cite web | title=Sahitya Academy Awards announced for the year 2013 | website=Jagranjosh.com | date=2013-12-19 | url=http://www.jagranjosh.com/current-affairs/sahitya-academy-awards-announced-for-the-year-2013-1387450119-1 | access-date=2017-10-17}}</ref> He also received the [[Sahitya Gaurav Puraskar]] for Sindhi language in 2011.<ref name="dna 2011">{{cite web | title=11 littérateurs awarded Sahitya Gaurav Puraskar in Ahmedabad | website=dna | date=2011-07-11 | url=http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-11-litt-rateurs-awarded-sahitya-gaurav-puraskar-in-ahmedabad-1564719 | access-date=2017-10-17}}</ref>
