{{Hatnote|Not to be confused with the [[Votic language]], which is Finnic.}} {{Infobox language family |name=Votic |region=Costa Rica, Nicaragua |familycolor=American |fam1 = [[Chibchan]] |glotto=voti1248 |glottorefname=Votic Chibchan }}
The '''Votic languages''' are a well-defined branch of [[Chibchan languages]] spoken in [[Costa Rica]] and [[Nicaragua]]. They are: *[[Rama language|Rama]] southeastern Nicaragua, extinct or nearly so *[[Voto language|Voto]] Costa Rica, extinct *[[Maléku language|Maléku]] (Guatuso) north-central Costa Rica, endangered *[[Corobicí language|Corobicí]] northwestern Costa Rica, extinct
